# Docker Integration Plan

## Goal Description
Integrate Docker into the existing Vite + React application to enable containerized development and deployment. This includes creating a production-ready `Dockerfile` using a multi-stage build (Node.js for building, Nginx for serving) and a `docker-compose.yml` for easy orchestration.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> Detailed Docker configuration provided below. No breaking changes to existing code.

## Proposed Changes

### Root Directory

#### [NEW] [Dockerfile](file:///C:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/landing-page---v3/Dockerfile)
- **Stage 1 (Build):**
  - Base image: `node:22-alpine` (matching project's @types/node version)
  - Install dependencies (`npm ci`)
  - Copy source code
  - Run build script (`npm run build`)
- **Stage 2 (Production):**
  - Base image: `nginx:alpine`
  - Copy build output (`dist`) to Nginx html directory
  - Copy custom `nginx.conf`

#### [NEW] [docker-compose.yml](file:///C:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/landing-page---v3/docker-compose.yml)
- Define `app` service
- Map port 8080 (host) to 80 (container)
- Mount volume for development (optional context, but focused on production build here)

#### [NEW] [.dockerignore](file:///C:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/landing-page---v3/.dockerignore)
- Exclude `node_modules`, `dist`, `.git`, local env files

#### [NEW] [nginx.conf](file:///C:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/landing-page---v3/nginx.conf)
- Serve static files with efficient caching
- Enable Gzip compression
- SPA fallback to [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/landing-page---v3/index.html) (future-proofing)

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `docker compose build` to verify the image builds successfully.
- Run `docker compose up -d` to start the container.
- `curl http://localhost:8080` to verify the server is responding.

### Manual Verification
- Access `http://localhost:8080` in the browser.
- Verify the landing page loads correctly.
- Verify assets (JS/CSS) load without 404s.
